1
00:00:00,297 --> 00:00:01,977
They came to call out the names

2
00:00:02,445 --> 00:00:03,586
So they called my name

3
00:00:05,031 --> 00:00:08,438
They told us that anyone under sixteen years old

4
00:00:11,055 --> 00:00:14,555
Was ordered released by the one they called “the judge”

5
00:00:16,203 --> 00:00:17,352
And indeed they took us down

6
00:00:17,828 --> 00:00:19,234
We were seven or eight people

7
00:00:19,259 --> 00:00:21,367
They took us down the stairs to here

8
00:00:22,766 --> 00:00:25,063
There were prisoners here, blindfolded

9
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,680
They were right here

10
00:00:27,132 --> 00:00:29,063
We stood with them and they started bringing us in one by one

11
00:00:29,234 --> 00:00:30,242
Interviewer: How many were you?

12
00:00:31,055 --> 00:00:32,781
We were about seven or eight people

13
00:00:33,086 --> 00:00:34,633
And we were taken in one after another

14
00:00:35,813 --> 00:00:37,320
My turn came, so I went in

15
00:00:37,547 --> 00:00:39,680
They brought me in and made me sit there

16
00:00:39,984 --> 00:00:41,039
One of them sat in front of me

17
00:00:42,643 --> 00:00:44,292
He asked me about the charge against me, and I told him it was robbery

18
00:00:45,894 --> 00:00:48,722
Then he asked me what kind of robbery

19
00:00:48,747 --> 00:00:49,675
I told him it was robbery from my uncle’s house

20
00:00:50,870 --> 00:00:53,073
And that the house had been confiscated

21
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:54,753
After he learned that

22
00:00:54,878 --> 00:00:55,925
He ordered that we be sent back inside

23
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:57,386
Meaning upstairs

24
00:00:57,964 --> 00:01:00,284
So they sent me back along with three others

25
00:01:00,808 --> 00:01:01,831
And the rest were released

26
00:01:02,644 --> 00:01:04,534
They took us back to the hall upstairs

27
00:01:04,644 --> 00:01:07,292
The three halls upstairs were empty at the time

28
00:01:07,886 --> 00:01:09,691
Only three of us remained

29
00:01:10,659 --> 00:01:12,456
The others were also convicted of theft

30
00:01:14,222 --> 00:01:17,394
We spent about two days in the hall

31
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:23,378
Then they told us the judge had ruled to release us, and they asked us to go with them

32
00:01:23,670 --> 00:01:25,654
Interviewer: Before they released you

33
00:01:27,123 --> 00:01:29,474
And specifically in the investigation room

34
00:01:30,545 --> 00:01:35,357
Were you blindfolded while you spoke with the judge?

35
00:01:35,382 --> 00:01:36,732
Could you see them, or did they prevent you?

36
00:01:36,857 --> 00:01:38,693
I was blindfolded and did not see them

37
00:01:43,053 --> 00:01:46,349
Interviewer: Were you able to identify the person who spoke with you?

38
00:01:46,545 --> 00:01:52,263
And did the interrogation involve any kind of insults or abuse?

39
00:01:53,342 --> 00:01:56,537
No, he just asked me about my charge, and I answered that it was theft

40
00:01:56,779 --> 00:01:59,950
Then he asked me what kind of theft—whether it was a motorcycle

41
00:01:59,998 --> 00:02:03,825
I told him, No, it was robbing a house with “confiscated” written on it

42
00:02:04,623 --> 00:02:06,185
So he ordered that I be sent back upstairs

43
00:02:06,381 --> 00:02:07,428
And they did

44
00:02:07,779 --> 00:02:09,881
I stayed upstairs for two days

45
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:13,592
Then they came to take me when the release decision came out

46
00:02:14,146 --> 00:02:15,295
And they asked me to go with them

47
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:22,263
Interviewer: Did they threaten you with execution or harming your family during the interrogation?

48
00:02:22,795 --> 00:02:25,342
Or with long prison terms if you didn’t confess, for example?

49
00:02:26,068 --> 00:02:28,053
They threatened to kill me if I did not confess

50
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,006
Meaning my execution

51
00:02:30,435 --> 00:02:31,810
Interviewer: And that was when you were in prison?

52
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,099
Yes, in prison

53
00:02:34,622 --> 00:02:35,591
Interviewer: Do you mean the previous prison?

54
00:02:35,646 --> 00:02:37,959
Yes, they told me that if I didn’t confess, they would behead me

55
00:02:39,193 --> 00:02:41,404
They said, "If you don’t confess, we’ll cut off your head"

56
00:02:47,842 --> 00:02:49,592
Interviewer: When you entered the investigation room

57
00:02:49,974 --> 00:02:52,967
Were you able to tell how many ISIS members were standing around you?

58
00:02:53,349 --> 00:02:57,771
Could you see anything from under the blindfold?

59
00:02:58,045 --> 00:02:59,123
What did you notice?

60
00:02:59,662 --> 00:03:03,248
There were chairs here

61
00:03:03,342 --> 00:03:04,654
And an ISIS member sat in front of me

62
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:07,013
So I tried to lift my head, but the ISIS member ordered me to lower it and not raise it again

63
00:03:07,576 --> 00:03:11,053
I tried that twice, but he hit me and ordered me not to raise my head

64
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,029
So I stayed standing without moving

65
00:03:13,178 --> 00:03:13,958
Interviewer: Was he the judge?

66
00:03:14,115 --> 00:03:16,740
No, he was another member, while the judge sat in front of me

67
00:03:18,334 --> 00:03:19,568
After some time, he ordered me to sit

68
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,615
So I sat on my knees

69
00:03:22,373 --> 00:03:23,263
I sat on the floor

70
00:03:23,288 --> 00:03:23,935
Interviewer: What went on between you?

71
00:03:24,013 --> 00:03:26,732
He asked me about the type of charge

72
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:28,154
I answered that it was theft

73
00:03:28,545 --> 00:03:31,178
There was a small bell next to him

74
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,857
He pressed the bell, so someone came

75
00:03:33,131 --> 00:03:35,685
The judge ordered him to take me back upstairs, so he did

76
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:43,888
Interviewer: During the interrogation, did they offer you to work with them as a spy?

77
00:03:44,162 --> 00:03:46,122
Whether outside or inside the prison

78
00:03:46,147 --> 00:03:48,880
Meaning to become a spy among the prisoners or even outside the prison

79
00:03:48,905 --> 00:03:49,919
As a condition for your release?

80
00:03:50,256 --> 00:03:52,521
Did they threaten to harm your family members?

81
00:03:52,834 --> 00:03:55,342
No, they didn’t threaten me like that

82
00:03:57,248 --> 00:04:00,310
Interviewer: Did you feel anything unusual during the interrogation?

83
00:04:00,529 --> 00:04:03,849
Were they recording your voice or filming you, for example?

84
00:04:04,263 --> 00:04:07,326
Did you feel something like that while you were blindfolded?

85
00:04:07,351 --> 00:04:08,646
I felt that when I was in prison

86
00:04:09,685 --> 00:04:11,107
I felt they were recording my voice

87
00:04:11,537 --> 00:04:12,818
I mean at Dawasa Prison

88
00:04:13,771 --> 00:04:15,240
Then they transferred us here

89
00:04:15,592 --> 00:04:17,029
Interviewer: And here you didn’t feel anything unusual

90
00:04:17,092 --> 00:04:18,162
No, I didn’t feel that

91
00:04:19,209 --> 00:04:20,795
Interviewer: What did this room look like then?

92
00:04:21,178 --> 00:04:23,357
It was clean and furnished

93
00:04:23,412 --> 00:04:24,834
And there was a TV screen

94
00:04:25,615 --> 00:04:27,357
They showed ISIS videos on it

95
00:04:27,912 --> 00:04:31,185
Videos and jihadi chants

96
00:04:31,881 --> 00:04:33,990
Interviewer: What else was in the room?

97
00:04:35,654 --> 00:04:37,435
The judge was sitting here

98
00:04:37,865 --> 00:04:40,295
There were seats, bedding, and the TV screen

99
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:42,787
And the equipment and weapons were all here

100
00:04:47,115 --> 00:04:50,490
Interviewer: What happened after they took you upstairs?

101
00:04:51,537 --> 00:04:56,428
The halls were empty and I stayed there with two other people

102
00:04:56,873 --> 00:04:59,131
Interviewer: What kind of theft were the ones with you accused of?

103
00:04:59,553 --> 00:05:01,873
One of them broke into a shop

104
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:07,357
And the other had previously been sentenced to a hand amputation, but they brought him here again

105
00:05:07,529 --> 00:05:09,138
For theft too, and this time they amputated his leg

106
00:05:10,428 --> 00:05:11,428
Interviewer: Did you know them?

107
00:05:11,453 --> 00:05:12,459
No, I didn’t

108
00:05:18,303 --> 00:05:24,310
Interviewer: Do you remember how many ISIS members spoke with you?

109
00:05:24,335 --> 00:05:25,959
Do you remember their nationalities?

110
00:05:26,029 --> 00:05:28,662
And do you remember the nationality of the <i>sharia</i> judge?

111
00:05:28,873 --> 00:05:31,842
Or their names, for example?

112
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:34,834
I don’t know them, but the one who was sitting here

113
00:05:35,326 --> 00:05:36,467
He was heavily built

114
00:05:37,029 --> 00:05:39,545
His beard was long and red

115
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:40,584
He had dyed it red

116
00:05:41,365 --> 00:05:42,607
I don’t know what they called him

117
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,271
Interviewer: What was his nationality?

118
00:05:44,748 --> 00:05:45,779
Syrian, I think

119
00:05:47,107 --> 00:05:48,740
Interviewer: Did you sense that from the way he spoke?

120
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:49,779
Yes
